hydra-llm (0.2.11-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Chat-model autokill (idle-TTL) now actually works. A new user-level
    systemd timer `hydra-llm-reaper.timer` ticks every 60s and runs
    `hydra-llm reap`, which stops chat-model containers that have been
    idle longer than `chat_idle_ttl_seconds` (default: 600s / 10 min;
    set to 0 to disable). The timer is enabled automatically by
    `hydra-llm setup`; manage it explicitly with
    `hydra-llm reaper {status,enable,disable}`.
  * "Idle" combines two signals so it works for both `hydra-llm chat`
    users and external API clients (Aider, curl, lillycoder, the
    Plasma widget): every chat turn refreshes a per-alias touch file,
    AND each reap cycle samples `docker stats` and treats any
    container above `reap_cpu_busy_percent` (default 1%) as in use,
    refreshing the touch on the spot.
  * Resource cost: the timer wakes once a minute, runs `docker ps` +
    one `docker stats --no-stream` for the running set, and exits.
    Cheap enough to leave on by default; no long-lived hydra process
    sits in memory between ticks.
  * New `hydra-llm reap` runs one autokill cycle synchronously (also
    used as the timer's ExecStart). New `hydra-llm reaper` group
    installs/removes the user systemd units and reports status.
  * `paths.MODEL_TOUCH_DIR` (`~/.local/state/hydra-llm/model-touch/`)
    holds one zero-byte file per alias whose mtime is the last
    observed activity, mirroring the existing embedder touch-dir.

 -- Ramazan Yavuz <yavuzramazan1994@gmail.com>  Fri, 08 May 2026 12:33:00 +0000

hydra-llm (0.2.10-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * `hydra-llm chat --new` allocates a fresh session file for the
    current (cwd, alias) and makes it the default for next time.
    Old sessions are kept; list them with `hydra-llm session list`.
    Implementation: a sidecar pointer file
    `<cwd_hash>-<alias>.current` records which session the next
    plain `chat <alias>` should resume. Without a pointer, behavior
    falls back to the legacy single-file shape so pre-0.2.10 sessions
    keep resuming as before.
  * `hydra-llm chat --clean` enumerates every session file for the
    current (cwd, alias), prints them with sizes, asks for
    confirmation, and removes them (plus the pointer file).
  * New `hydra-llm session` group: `list`, `show`, `load`, `rm`.
    `list` defaults to sessions in the current cwd; `--all` shows
    everything. `load <name-or-path>` switches the per-folder
    default. `show` dumps the JSON message log in human-readable
    form. `rm` removes one (with confirmation).
  * `hydra-llm chat --persona "..."` accepts inline prompt text
    when the argument doesn't resolve to a persona file. The
    heuristic (must contain whitespace or sentence punctuation, or
    be unusually long) keeps a typo'd slug like 'firendly-tutor'
    from silently becoming a one-word persona. A misspelled slug
    still raises FileNotFoundError as before.

