hydra-llm (0.2.8-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Catalog now ships sha256 for every entry. The downloader has
    verified-on-download since v0.2.6, but the field was empty in
    catalog/catalog.yaml and catalog/embedders.yaml so the check
    was a no-op in practice. Backfilled via Hugging Face's tree API
    (the `lfs.oid` field on every LFS-stored GGUF *is* sha256 by
    spec), so no bandwidth was spent computing hashes from local
    downloads. From now on, a corrupt or partial download fails
    loudly during `hydra-llm download` instead of silently
    producing a broken local model that crashes at first load.
  * `scripts/sha256-backfill.py` learned the HF API mode. The
    streaming-download mode is still there as `--full-download`
    for non-HF URLs; it's just no longer the default.
  * Roadmap pruned: the Plasma RAG widget tab item is gone (won't
    do), and the SHA backfill item is gone (shipped).

