hydra-llm (0.2.7-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Fix regression in v0.2.6 where `hydra-llm chat` could fail to
    launch a slow-loading big model. The new chat-model auto-recover
    wrapper waited 30 seconds for /health before bailing out;
    16-30 GB GGUFs on iGPU spillover routinely take longer than that
    to load. The wrapper now only watches for the corrupt-GGUF crash
    signature inside a brief early window (5 seconds), then hands off
    to the existing 300-second log-streamed wait in chat.py for the
    actual readiness check.
  * Better diagnostics when a chat container fails to come up. The
    "[server did not become healthy]" / "[container exited before
    becoming healthy]" paths now also dump `docker inspect` state
    (status, exit code, OOMKilled flag) and the last 30 log lines so
    the user can tell at a glance whether the kernel killed it for
    OOM, llama.cpp aborted, or something else.
  * `hydra-llm chat` no longer auto-attaches to an exited container
    that happens to share an alias. An exited container's port is
    stale and `start_model` would refuse to recreate it because of
    the name collision; we now treat exited as "needs fresh start".
  * The "pick one to start" picker annotates each row with a VRAM-fit
    verdict (`fits VRAM` / `spills` / `won't fit`), computed against
    `hardware.fits_locally`, so users don't blindly pick a model that
    overruns their GPU.
  * `hydra-llm --version` now reports the right version. v0.2.6
    shipped with `__version__ = "0.2.5"` because the constant in
    `lib/hydra_llm/__init__.py` is bumped separately from the .deb's
    `debian/changelog`. RELEASE.md grew a "Things that have bitten
    us before" entry to remind us next time.

 -- Ramazan Yavuz <yavuzramazan1994@gmail.com>  Fri, 08 May 2026 10:24:48 +0000

hydra-llm (0.2.6-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * `help` now works as a subverb everywhere. `hydra-llm rag help`,
    `hydra-llm chat help`, `hydra-llm rag setup help` and so on print
    the relevant help text instead of erroring out. Group parsers
    (`rag`, `persona`) get a real `help` child verb that also accepts
    a sub-subcommand topic; leaf parsers honor the convention via a
    one-line argv rewrite so no per-leaf changes were needed.
  * New `hydra-llm rag explain` prints a concise primer on how RAG
    works in hydra: per-folder LanceDB indexes at
    `<folder>/.hydra-index/`, the global stores registry, and how to
    retrieve from a different folder or federate across many. Linked
    from the top of `hydra-llm rag --help`.
  * `hydra-llm chat` no longer tries to auto-attach to embedder
    sidecars. Embedder containers share the chat-model name root so
    the docker name filter caught both; `list_running` now excludes
    them at source, fixing the `embed-* unknown alias` foot-gun.
  * Content-aware embedder pick on first index. When the user has not
    named an embedder explicitly and the folder has no `.hydra-index/`
    yet, `hydra-llm index` peeks at the file mix and offers a better
    default: nomic-embed-text on >80% prose folders, qwen3-embed-4b
    on code/mixed. Genuinely mixed corpora get a one-line
    `--dual-index` hint.
  * `hydra-llm rag stores --path P --tag-add foo` (and `--tag-remove`)
    retag an existing store without reindexing it.
  * Saved store collections. `hydra-llm rag collections save NAME
    --path P --tag T` records a named federation; chat and query then
    accept `--rag-collection NAME` instead of repeating the same
    paths/tags every invocation.
  * Embedder idle-TTL reaper. Every embed call touches a per-alias
    timestamp file under `$XDG_STATE_HOME/hydra-llm/embedder-touch/`;
    on the next CLI invocation hydra stops sidecars idle longer than
    `embedder_idle_ttl_seconds`. The config key existed since 0.2.x
    with a 60-second default; only the enforcement was missing.
  * `hydra-llm doctor` now reports the engine image age and the
    llama.cpp ref it was built from (the LABEL added in v0.2.5), so
    a user troubleshooting a model-load failure can see at a glance
    when their image was built.
  * Chat-model auto-recover on corrupt GGUF. The same auto-redownload
    pattern that was added for embedder sidecars in v0.2.5 now wraps
    chat-model startup: if the container fails to come up and the
    logs match the corrupt-GGUF signature, hydra deletes the local
    GGUF, re-downloads, and retries once.
  * Resumable downloads. The downloader now sends a `Range` header
    when a `.part` file is present from a previous interrupted
    download, falls back gracefully if the server refuses the range,
    and leaves the partial file in place on network drop so the next
    attempt picks up where the last one stopped.
  * `hydra-llm addlocal --prefix <slug>` prepends a slug to derived
    ids in folder mode and single-file mode, taking the edge off
    long Hugging-Face filenames.
  * Chat session save line is now conditional. `[session saved]`
    only prints if the current REPL produced new messages.
  * apt source line in install instructions pins
    `arch=amd64,arm64`, suppressing the harmless but noisy `i386`
    skip warning on machines with i386 as a foreign dpkg architecture.
  * `scripts/sha256-backfill.py` (dev tool, not shipped) walks the
    catalog YAMLs, computes sha256 of each upstream URL by streaming,
    and writes the values back so the downloader's existing
    verification path stops being a no-op.

