hydra-llm (0.2.4-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Engine images are now built against a pinned llama.cpp commit
    instead of git master at install time. The Dockerfiles previously
    cloned `--branch master --depth 1` whenever a user ran
    `hydra-llm setup`, which made each install a one-off snapshot
    against whatever was on master that day. With the pin, every user
    gets the same image; bumping llama.cpp is a hydra-release decision
    and reproducibility is guaranteed.
  * `hydra-llm setup --rebuild` forces a from-scratch rebuild of the
    engine image even when one already exists locally. Useful after a
    hydra-llm upgrade if a new release bumped the pin and you want
    the new image without waiting for it to be re-needed.
  * The repo URL also moved from ggerganov/llama.cpp to
    ggml-org/llama.cpp (the canonical upstream as of mid-2026).
  * Pinned to llama.cpp e43431b38115 (HEAD as of 2026-05-07). Tested
    end to end with Qwen3-Embedding-4B-Q4_K_M.gguf (which had been
    failing to load on stale engines because the GGUF parser had
    not yet learned a metadata key Qwen3 emits).

