hydra-llm (0.2.2-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * hydra-llm-plasma: relax Depends so the plasmoid installs on every
    Plasma 6 system regardless of how distros name their QML6 modules.
    Previously the plasmoid hard-required
    qml6-module-org-kde-plasma-components by that exact Debian-style
    name, which Ubuntu 26.04 (resolute) does not ship; apt would
    refuse the whole transaction. Now: only hydra-llm itself is a
    Depends; QML modules and plasma-workspace are Recommends, so a
    missing module causes graceful runtime degradation instead of an
    install-time refusal.
  * Net effect: `apt upgrade` no longer rolls back the CLI upgrade
    just because the plasmoid couldn't be solved on the user's
    distro. The CLI is the main thing; the plasmoid is optional.

