    registers every .gguf under it. Group flags (--tier, --family,
    --license, --gpu-layers, --ram-gb, --vram-gb) apply to all entries.
    Saves users the tedious one-by-one for a folder of weights from
    Ollama / LM Studio / a manual download.
  * `get.sh` (the bash one-liner installer) offers to apt-install
    docker.io on Debian/Ubuntu when docker is missing, instead of just
    warning. User still has to run `usermod -aG docker $USER` and log
    out/in themselves; the script prints the exact line.
