    replaced with a small note that links to the full disclaimer at
    the bottom (so first-time visitors are not greeted with a wall of
    fearful warnings). New "Why Docker" section explains the engine
    choice; new "Where it runs" section documents Linux / WSL2 /
    macOS / headless support.
  * Hub card gains a RAG badge and the body copy spells out
    "retrieval-augmented generation" once.
  * Profile README and project README both mention RAG positioning
    and the full term explicitly so search engines and skim-readers
    can anchor on it.
