hydra-llm (0.1.6-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Catalog resolver now accepts a GGUF filename (with or without the
    `.gguf` extension) anywhere a catalog id is taken: `start`, `stop`,
    `download`, `chat`, `api`, etc. Exact match; id wins on collisions.
  * New `hydra-llm autostart [id]` subcommand. Writes a user-level
    systemd unit (`~/.config/systemd/user/hydra-llm-autostart.service`)
    that runs `hydra-llm start <id>` when you log in. Run with no
    args to see current state. `hydra-llm autostart --off` removes
    the unit. No root needed; the model id stays in user config.

